title: SpaceX launches eighth dedicated smallsat rideshare mission
summary: SpaceX launched its eighth dedicated smallsat rideshare mission, Transporter-8, carrying 72 payloads including satellites from established companies like Spire, Iceye, and Satellogic, as well as first-time satellite deployments from startups. The mission also included payloads from the U.S. Space Force and DARPA.
